<db:section xml:id="elidedText-method">
<db:title>string elidedText(string <db:emphasis>text</db:emphasis>, enumeration <db:emphasis>mode</db:emphasis>, real <db:emphasis>width</db:emphasis>, int <db:emphasis>flags</db:emphasis>)</db:title>
<db:para>This method returns an elided version of the string (i.e., a string with &quot;...&quot; in it) if the string <db:code role="parameter">text</db:code> is wider than <db:code role="parameter">width</db:code>. Otherwise, returns the original string.</db:para>
<db:para>The <db:code role="parameter">mode</db:code> argument specifies the text elide mode; that is, where the ellipsis should appear when displaying text that doesn't fit.</db:para>
<db:para>The <db:code role="parameter">flags</db:code> argument is optional and currently only supports <db:link xlink:href="qt.xml#TextFlag-enum">Qt::TextShowMnemonic</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:para>This method is offered as an imperative alternative to the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-textmetrics.xml#elidedText-prop">elidedText</db:link> property of <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-textmetrics.xml">TextMetrics</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:section>
